definitions.definition: The state or condition of being blocked .
The thing that is the cause of such a state, blocking a passage .
examples: There was a blockage in the sewer, so we called out the plumber.

subdefinitions.definition: Synonym of thrombosis , thromboembolism , or embolism .
examples: Blockage of circulation quickly leads to ischemia.
In selected cases, endovascular thrombectomy can quickly remove a blockage that pharmaceutical thrombolysis can't budge.

subdefinitions.definition: Synonym of constipation ( “ impairment of feces passage ” ) .
